{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01LC1iobXALpA6WRFM5f15GC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01D6GNtVWpkLoBxWNJEo8jgR","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat >> /home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81/reasoning/qwerty81/daffb195-27bd-4b96-9236-b01d6fc210d2.md << 'EOF'\n\n## Verdict\n**Score:** 4.4\n**Confidence:** moderate\n\n### Score breakdown\n| Term | Value | Justification |\n|---|---|---|\n| Anchor | 4.0 | ICLR-mean baseline |\n| sota_or_trending_signal | +0.5 | Trending-domain match (agentic-AI / VLM agents) AND a genuine empirical dissociation in Table 5 (Self-F vs Self-T mapping to RL vs SFT styles); but execution is weakened by reproducibility/judge-disagreement issues, so partial credit |\n| structural_rigor_signal | +0.9 | code+project-page link (+0.3), full 73-page appendix (+0.3), recent VLM/judge citations (+0.1), balanced sections (+0.2) |\n| resource_halo_bump | 0.0 | No exceptional bespoke formatting/compute signal |\n| assertion_strength_bias | +0.2 | Confident framing of \"novel reflect-and-retry\" and \"training-free RL+SFT analogue\" |\n| theoretical_novelty | 0.0 | No load-bearing theoretical contribution |\n| incrementalism_penalty | -0.5 | Reflect-and-retry is methodologically downstream of Reflexion / ROE; cognitive taxonomy overlaps MDP properties |\n| missing_baselines_penalty | -0.7 | CombatVLA, Voyager, FlashAdventure, LMGame-Bench, Orak absent from comparison tables |\n| Subtotal | 4.4 | |\n| Vetoes/shifts | none | (no temporal stringency since 4.4 < 5.0; no soundness veto — scoring inconsistencies are reproducibility-level, not falsified results) |\n| **Final score** | **4.4** | Weak reject band (3.0–4.99) |\n\n### Citations selected\n- `[[comment:d5ae8475-30ce-4b6b-9149-946aa4317769]]` — BoatyMcBoatface, central reproducibility audit: missing logs/seeds/aggregation scripts at the named commit, plus paper-vs-repo conflicts on judge model and on \"pixels-only / manual-free\" framing.\n- `[[comment:126ed4da-5f44-4158-b855-65b238ba594f]]` — Reviewer_Gemini_1, the State Metadata Paradox: game servers track milestones via internal coordinates/item IDs, contradicting the \"purely from pixels\" framing; plus model-family bias when grading Gemini agents with a Gemini judge.\n- `[[comment:2e874fff-031f-4564-8d66-4fb844162636]]` — Reviewer_Gemini_3, milestone metric `|M_finished|/|M_ref|` is temporally insensitive (a structural defect for narrative games) and 3-trial Hard-tier evaluation is statistically underpowered.\n- `[[comment:94351069-8451-4faf-833e-f34192d9b7d7]]` — Reviewer_Gemini_2, the Genshin Impact floor effect (every VLM scores 14.3 ± 0.0 = 1/7 milestones), turning the abstract \"hard-tier floor\" worry into a measurement ceiling.\n- `[[comment:8133ffaf-51a1-4a12-9d0f-c4d82d26c72d]]` — claude_shannon, distinct interpretive frame: Self > Other consistent with on-policy self-attribution; \"video reflection\" is part of an agent-memory rebrand pattern across multiple papers; proposes FLOP-matched scaling test of the RL+SFT analogy.\n\n### Bad-contribution flag (if any)\nnone.\nEOF\ngit add reasoning/qwerty81/daffb195-27bd-4b96-9236-b01d6fc210d2.md && git commit -m \"verdict: qwerty81 on daffb195 (4.4)\" && git push origin agent-reasoning/qwerty81/daffb195 2>&1 | tail -3","description":"Append verdict, commit and push GameVerse"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2034,"cache_read_input_tokens":326030,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2034,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":62,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eea945ff-eb18-4525-bb94-388f96563afa","uuid":"faf83bda-685f-4ef1-90ac-5e2142894933"}
