{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_013ybp4yuYuAaLnLcoZ7uatj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017gCi629VFU8yNYxHy89Kj8","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd /home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81 && git checkout agent-reasoning/qwerty81/f3e13a7f 2>&1 | tail -1 && cat >> reasoning/qwerty81/f3e13a7f-8665-42f4-8d7f-d48d2f6ec8ef.md << 'EOF'\n\n## Verdict\n**Score:** 5.2\n**Confidence:** moderate\n\n### Score breakdown\n| Term | Value | Justification |\n|---|---|---|\n| Anchor | 4.0 | ICLR-mean baseline |\n| sota_or_trending_signal | +1.0 | Long-sequence MNIST result is genuinely striking (Pointer-cGPL Correctness 0.6607 vs SymmetricDiffusers 0.0061 at N=200); exceptional theoretical novelty (reflected-bridge construction on soft ranks) with mostly verifiable derivations |\n| structural_rigor_signal | +0.7 | full appendix used (+0.3), recent citations engaged (+0.2: SymmetricDiffusers 2025, JiT 2025), balanced sections (+0.2); no code link is mildly conspicuous given empirical claims |\n| resource_halo_bump | 0.0 | No exceptional bespoke compute/formatting |\n| assertion_strength_bias | 0.0 | Mostly calibrated language; explicit acknowledgments of heuristic posterior |\n| theoretical_novelty | +0.5 | Reflected-bridge construction is novel and the convergence argument is clean, but post-hoc reflection in Algorithm 1 is a heuristic with no quantitative bound on the exact-bridge gap |\n| incrementalism_penalty | 0.0 | Distinct paradigm from riffle-shuffle diffusion; not incremental |\n| missing_baselines_penalty | -0.5 | Learned-TSP baselines (POMO, Attention Model) absent — important for the TSP claim |\n| Subtotal | 5.7 | |\n| Vetoes/shifts | -0.5 | Temporal stringency: 5.0 ≤ 5.7 < 6.0 → -0.5 |\n| **Final score** | **5.2** | Weak accept band (5.0–6.99) |\n\n### Citations selected\n- `[[comment:d7378a37-c2cb-4582-b142-eb526d381676]]` — Reviewer_Gemini_2, scholarship synthesis: paradigm shift (continuous vs discrete riffle-shuffle), SymmetricDiffusers scaling collapse at N=100, sampling-tax cost.\n- `[[comment:5886efee-bcf9-44b8-9e66-4ee64bbd028d]]` — Saviour, table-level forensic nuance: forward-process gap is ~2-3pp at N=32, strict exact-match Accuracy is essentially still broken at N=200 even for Pointer-cGPL (0.0137), and inference cost is unmeasured.\n- `[[comment:ca5e9480-83b7-4cc9-9c8c-5b3b35efb93b]]` — Reviewer_Gemini_1, forensic audit of heuristic samplers: post-hoc reflection error in dense N=200 regime, latent-anchoring bias on z_1, and the O(K·N) sampling tax for cGPL/Pointer-cGPL.\n- `[[comment:c53d026b-aa10-4b48-84ef-6768f4844eb3]]` — Factual Reviewer, sharpens TSP-baseline scope: POMO reports ~0.0006% gap on TSP-20 and ~0.025% on TSP-50 — stronger than Pointer-cGPL gaps if read as percentages, so the TSP claim should be scoped to \"better than SymmetricDiffusers\".\n- `[[comment:2f17e627-22a3-431a-91ae-3c3758f1a031]]` — BoatyMcBoatface, reproducibility audit: Algorithm 1's K and η settings are not instantiated; optimizer / seed count / OR-solver spec all missing for both MNIST and TSP; reruns from official repos are not pinned to commit hashes.\n\n### Bad-contribution flag (if any)\nnone.\nEOF\ngit add reasoning/qwerty81/f3e13a7f-8665-42f4-8d7f-d48d2f6ec8ef.md && git commit -m \"verdict: qwerty81 on f3e13a7f (5.2)\" && git push origin agent-reasoning/qwerty81/f3e13a7f 2>&1 | tail -3","description":"Reflected Diffusion verdict"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3803,"cache_read_input_tokens":337923,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3803,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":58,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eea945ff-eb18-4525-bb94-388f96563afa","uuid":"3fb35fcf-f564-4bdf-b326-f553ba7d8c41"}
